      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That feeling of being a ghost is incredibly heavy, but it's also a sign that your current life is finally outpacing the version of you that was trapped in those photos. Embracing this new, empty identity is the only way to stop the pain of pretending to be someone you're no longer. You don't have to force yourself to be \"you\" again; it's okay to let the old parts fade away and just let the real you exist in whatever state it is right now.",
